ildlife and superb facilities for both day and overnight visitors.";i:11;s:119:"The garden route adventure guide is a comprehensive guide to adventure and outdoor activities in the garden route area.";i:12;s:36:"Book a half day or full day package.";i:13;s:136:"The garden route game lodge is set against the backdrop of the majestic langeberg mountain range on the breathtaking garden route coast.";i:14;s:157:"The garden route, situated along the southern coast of south africa, is a dream playground to anyone who loves the outdoors and with a passion for adventure.";i:15;s:237:"All reviews garden route game lodge cape town day safari breathtaking views great fun worth the price recommend this place take photos an amazing experience excellent service on arrival night stay our honeymoon guide lions drive animals.";i:16;s:132:"Only 3½ scenic hours drive from cape town, this malaria free, private game reserve is home to an abundance of animal and bird life.";i:17;s:34:"Fantastic safari for day visitors.";i:18;s:119:"Early bird game drive takes off just before sunrise which is around 6h50 during winter (r300pp) and 5h30 during summer.";i:19;s:66:"Conveniently located off the n2 between albertinia and mossel bay.";i:20;s:91:"The daily game drive options are ideal for the footloose, traveling along the garden route.";i:21;s:82:"Ist ein besuch dieser sehenswürdigkeit aufregend, ungewöhnlich oder gefährlich?";i:22;s:57:"2hr game drive = r490.00 per adult and r245.00 per child.";i:23;s:34:"1 von 3 aktivitäten in albertina.";i:24;s:165:"Enjoy a thrilling game drive in an open landrover with your experienced game ranger who will bring you sightings of lion, elephant, white rhino, buffalo and cheetah.";i:25;s:73:"This leisure area features a swimming pool for adults, a pool with water.";i:26;s:78:"The garden route officially starts in mossel bay and finishes in stormsrivier.";i:27;s:158:"Receive up to 30% off our full board package including luxury accommodation, 3 gourmet meals and 2 game drives per day and junior ranger program for children.";i:28;s:30:"Garden route safari camp home;";i:29;s:123:"Walk with wildlife in the klein karoo at swartberg game reserve, 45 minutes from oudshoorn and 20 minutes from cango caves.";i:30;s:58:"On the tour, you are likely to spot four out of the big 5;";i:31;s:187:"There is a kids' bushwise activity programme that includes game drives for children to get up close to wildlife, a guided bush walk and an insect walk or fishing in one of the waterholes.";i:32;s:141:"Garden route game lodge, a popular stop for travellers between cape town and mossel bay, has its main gates right on the n2, for easy access.";i:33;s:178:"Only 3½ scenic hours drive from cape town, this malaria free, family owned and operated private game reserve is home to an abundance of animal and bird life including the big 5.";i:34;s:49:"Game viewing drives last approximately 2½ hours.";i:35;s:128:"Indalu is a stunning game reserve situated just 20km from albertinia and 30km from mossel bay in the western cape, south africa.";i:36;s:146:"Here you can enjoy sightings of lion, rhino, giraffe, elephant and much more from the back of an open landrover in this malaria free game reserve.";i:37;s:88:"We offer day excursions and overnight safari package with several accommodation options.";i:38;s:81:"Visitors to the garden route game lodge can enjoy gameviewing in open landrovers.";i:39;s:39:"Lions, rhinos, elephants, and buffalos.";i:40;s:41:"Featured in our garden route safari blog.";i:41;s:50:"15% off between 01 october 2019 and 31 march 2020.";i:42;s:150:"The malaria free garden route game lodge offers day visitors a chance to experience some of africa’s wildlife as they journey down the garden route.";i:43;s:135:"The garden route game lodge offers day visitors a chance to experience some of africa's wildlife as they journey down the garden route.";i:44;s:71:"Read the blog from our recent visit here a day on safari @ botlierskop.";i:45;s:119:"However, day visitors are allowed into the reserve free of charge and can join the daily game drives at 11 am and 2 pm.";i:46;s:165:"Set against the backdrop of the majestic langeberg mountain range, the garden route game lodge guards the entrance to south africa's world famous garden route coast.";i:47;s:73:"Departs around 15h00 during winter season and around 16h00 during summer.";i:48;s:118:"At 3½ hours drive from cape town, the garden route game lodge is probably just too far for a day tour from cape town.";i:49;s:167:"Set against the backdrop of the majestic langeberg mountain range, the garden route game lodge guards the entrance to south africa’s world famous garden route coast.";i:50;s:103:"A la carte meals and garden route game drives can be booked with at least 24 hours notice at the lodge.";i:51;s:109:"We are situated along a magnificent coastline in one of the best adventure holiday destinations in the world.";i:52;s:36:"Garden route game lodge day safaris.";i:53;s:199:"The garden route lies between cape town and port elizabeth, and is one of the first areas that south africans recommend to visitors.it has stunning cliffs and beaches but also deep forests and lakes.";i:54;s:197:"Garden route game lodge, offering big 5 south african safari experience, is situated in the heartland of the world famous fynbos botanical route, offers you the big 5 in a malaria free environment.";i:55;s:108:"Not only do they offer 4 star rated accommodation and facilities, they also have a dedicated day center for.";i:56;s:64:"Staff are very friendly and you get really close to the animals.";i:57;s:394:"Set against the backdrop of the majestic langeberg mountain range, the garden route game lodge guards the entrance to south africa’s world famous garden route coast.only 3½ scenic hours drive from cape town, this malaria free, family owned and operated private game reserve is home to an abundance of animal and birdlife including the big 5.visitors to the garden route game lodge can enjoy.";i:58;s:106:"Don’t worry you won’t be bored here and you’ll never have too much time to explore the garden route.";i:59;s:128:"One departs in the early morning and the other in the late afternoon, since these are the times the animals are the most active.";i:60;s:87:"Enjoy big five safaris and be lucky to spot elephant, rhino, buffalo, lion and leopard.";i:61;s:120:"Only 3½ scenic hours drive from cape town, one hour from swellendam and 30 minutes from mossel bay on the garden route.";i:62;s:394:"Set against the backdrop of the majestic langeberg mountain range, the garden route game lodge guards the entrance to south africa’s world famous garden route coast.only 3½ scenic hours drive from cape town, this malaria free, family owned and operated private game reserve is home to an abundance of animal and birdlife including the big 5.visitors to the garden route game lodge can enjoy.";}}